Article detailing the whole evaluation has been submitted to      3649 1451
Nuclear Data Sheets. The preprint can be found in Ref. [1].       3649 1451
Below is a summary of the main                                    3649 1451
improvements:                                                     3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
Thermal and Resolved Resonance Region:                            3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
The major changes relative to the ENDF/B-VIII.0 resonances,       3649 1451
which had been taken from ENDF/B-VII.1, can be summarized         3649 1451
as follows:                                                       3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
 - Change of resonance format from Multi-Level Breit-Wigner       3649 1451
(MLBW) to Reich-Moore (RM) in total cross sections.               3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
 - Setting the scattering radius to match the value recommended   3649 1451
by the 2018 Atlas [2], that is  7.8 +/- 0.1 fm.                   3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
 - Adding the background artificial resonance at -20.0 keV        3649 1451
(adopted from JENDL-4.0 [3]), but with tuned capture width to     3649 1451
set thermal capture cross section at the value of 3 mb. At first  3649 1451
this may seem low, but it is worth noting that the 3 mb value     3649 1451
is based solely on measurements of 4 primary gammas.              3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
 - Adding a missing resonance at 188.89 keV from Carlton          3649 1451
et al. [4] using systematics for gamma width taken from           3649 1451
JENDL-4.0.                                                        3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
Overall agreement of 86Kr(n,tot) improved dramatically at high    3649 1451
energies on account of the format change, and at low energy       3649 1451
due to the new resonance and the change to scattering radius.     3649 1451
The capture cross section now goes though the thermal point.      3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
Fast Region:                                                      3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
Above the inelastic threshold, the nuclear reaction model code    3649 1451
EMPIRE-3.2.3 Malta (SVN rev.  5294; source rev.  5291) [5] was    3649 1451
employed.                                                         3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
For the total cross section the energy range was split in three   3649 1451
sections based on the reliability of the experimental data. For   3649 1451
each of them we adopted a different approach:                     3649 1451
1) Between 1-8 MeV: Legendre fit to data sets from Raman et al.   3649 1451
[6] and Carlton et al. [4].                                       3649 1451
2) Between 8-12 MeV: Separate Legendre fit to data from Carlton   3649 1451
et al. [4].                                                       3649 1451
3) Above 12 MeV: Koning-Delaroche optical model potential [7].    3649 1451
                                                                  3649 1451
Inelastic cross sections were constrained by adjustments to 12    3649 1451
inelastic gamma transitions from measurements of Fotiades et al.  3649 1451
[8]. For that the level structure from ENSDF [9] was              3649 1451
adopted and corrected by the measurements of Urban et al. [10].   3649 1451
Uncertain or missing spins, parities and/or branching ratios      3649 1451
were determined through systematics or cross-section              3649 1451
agreement.  The high-energy tail of inelastic was determined      3649 1451
by adjusting prequilibrium parameters so that the cross           3649 1451
sections for the (n,2n)85mKr reaction to match the data of        3649 1451
Bhike et al. [11].                                                3649 1451
